5) Duplicate IP means two devices use the same IP address in the network.

Problems:
    Network conflict
    Packet loss
    Connection instability
    Devices become unreachable
Detection:
    System shows message like
    IP address conflict detected
Resolution:
    Assign unique IP addresses
    Use DHCP instead of manual IP

6)1. Remote Access using VNC Viewer
Aim

To access and control a remote computer using VNC Viewer.

Requirements

Two systems connected to the same network

VNC Server installed on the remote system

VNC Viewer installed on the client system

Step-by-Step Procedure
Step 1: Install VNC Server on the Remote Machine

On the remote computer, download and install VNC Server.

For Ubuntu/Linux:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install tightvncserver

Start the VNC server:

tightvncserver

During startup it will ask for a password for remote access.

Step 2: Find the IP Address of the Remote Machine

Run the command:

ip addr

Example output:

inet 192.168.1.20

This is the IP address of the remote system.

Step 3: Install VNC Viewer on Client Machine

Download VNC Viewer from:

https://www.realvnc.com

Install the software.

Step 4: Connect to the Remote System

Open VNC Viewer.

Enter the address:

192.168.1.20:5900

Where

192.168.1.20 → remote system IP

5900 → default VNC port

Step 5: Authenticate

Enter the VNC password that was created earlier.

Step 6: Remote Desktop Opens

The remote computer desktop will appear on the client system.

You can now:

Control mouse and keyboard

Run applications

Transfer files

