4. Remote Access using Windows Remote Desktop (RDP)
Aim

To access a Windows computer remotely using Remote Desktop Protocol.

Step-by-Step Procedure
Step 1: Enable Remote Desktop

On the remote Windows system:

Open Settings

Go to System

Click Remote Desktop

Enable Allow Remote Desktop

Step 2: Find the IP Address

Open Command Prompt and run:

ipconfig

Example:

IPv4 Address : 192.168.1.20
Step 3: Open Remote Desktop on Client

Press:

Windows + R

Type:

mstsc

Press Enter.

Step 4: Enter Remote IP Address

In the Remote Desktop window type:

192.168.1.20

Click Connect.

Step 5: Login

Enter the username and password of the remote computer.

Step 6: Remote Desktop Opens

You can now control the remote system.








